    <note>Li(2) Zhuanzheng [1009] Shoupeng's [1085] son, Fugui's [1024] nephew, Ruogu's [1046] great grandson. Lineage data in XNYL. I am going to assume that he is the father of Chuquan [16814], etc. and that he moved to Liyang. He is probably an uncle of Chulian [16819], father-in-law of Han(1) An [16822] (q.v.), who is identified by generational name. The previous affinal ties between the Han(1) and Li(2) would seem to support this hypothesis. Chuquan is listed as a Fengxian resident, great grandson of Shu [3528], who moved to Jiangning, Liyang, whereas his brothers, Chumai [16816] and Chuduan [16815], are identified as Luoyang residents. Probable cousin, Chulian, was a disciple of Cheng(1) Yi [3105], which suggest that there was a possible move from Fengxian to Luoyang and then to Liyang. Another great grandson of Shu, Chuquan(2) [16818], who also moved to Liyang, died in 1155 at an age of more than 70, which would tie in chronologicaly with Chulian, who was clearly older than Chuquan and his brothers. I am, therefore, making Zhuangzheng the father of Chuquan and his brothers and uncle of Chulian and Chuquan. The kin ties between Chuquan and Chuquan(2) are clear since Chuquan composed the preface to Chuquan(2)'s collected papers. I am not interpolating a move to Luoyang. XNYL, 6.27a, 8.14a; SHY:SH, 47.13b.</note>
